race.description: Club Taree City Panthers Cup Handicap (C3)
race.comment: Strong contest with plenty of different form angles. EDGE OF MIDNIGHT (2) rewarded for his consistency when jumping in trip for a tough victory over 1206m at Port Macquarie. Gets a similar set-up and only jumps 1kg in weight. GET SOME FUN (6) sent to town at her second run back when a tenacious on-pace fifth over 1200m at Rosehill in Highway grade. Ready to peak and can go forward from the draw. Each way. DE FORZA (1) has gone to a new level this time in and far from disgraced when a tiring seventh over 1200m at Rosehill in Highway class. Proven at this track and trip and can bounce back with the claim. KEVIN MCKEEN (8) returned from the lengthy break with the two solid minor placings. Drops in weight and maps to get the right run. FOUR DEGREES (3) stretches out to the 1250m for the first time and near her peak. Drawn out and will need luck from the draw.
